cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.SE

This paper discusses the development of a censorship-resistant infrastructure, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The infrastructure involves encapsulating traffic within email messages, which utilizes network infrastructure (cs.NI) and distributed systems (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the feasibility of the system in terms of censorship resistance (cs.CY) and performance (cs.SE).
